Golf mirrors life in so many ways…

Now, like any rational human, I didn’t go looking for this “situation,” but…

Here we are 🤷🏽‍♂️

AND THIS is why I love golf so much!

Just like smooth seas don’t make a great sailor, picking up the ball and moving it, quitting on a hole, or just throwing another ball down and pretending it didn’t happen won’t make you a better golfer either.

(You also don’t get good at something if you’re not willing to LEARN HOW to overcome it 💡💡)

And TRUST me, I’ve been “in the woods” a plenty!!

My point is:

GO to the course.

TAKE the shot.

and either WIN or LEARN.

I promise you’ll miss 100% of the shots you don’t take.

O.O.D.A.

👀Observe
✅Orient
🔥Decide
👊🏼Act

We’ve all heard that taking imperfect action trumps perfect inaction every time, and it’s one of those things that on the surface makes sense too.
The trouble is, most of us DON’T do that.

It isn’t because we can’t and it isn’t because we won’t.
It’s because we have cognitive dissonance with the idea.

See, our entire lives, whenever we’ve tried something and failed, the feedback has mostly been negative.
Either from those in authority, or worse yet, from our worst enemy, ourselves.

Who in the hell wants to repeat behaviors that HURT so badly?

This is where UNDERSTANDING how to stack the odds in your favor comes in. 
This is where KNOWING the statistics for the actions that lead to the MOST FAVORABLE outcome is paramount.

This is where we find the motivation for DISCIPLINE and consistent action has the best opportunity to yield the results we want.
Stay with me here.
The idea of OODA is from the military. Top brass noticed that their pilots with the most planes shot down ALSO fired the most shots.

They “wasted” more ammo but also had more success.
What they learned from this was the FASTER you can make a decision, learn from them, and evolve, the more likely you are to win.

See, it’s okay to waste more bullets because it’s what wins the war.

When you learn to:
Observe the challenge
Orient yourself
Decide your next move
Act and Fire

You will put yourself into the OODA loop of success and thereby more likely win.
The challenge is to recognize your resistance to making quick decisions and acting on them.

It’s also in learning to let what DOESN’T work go, and let it go quickly.

Hope this helps you in understanding how you can rapidly evolve and evolve quickly.
Remember, we’re here to win the war...leave the battles to the small-minded thinkers who don’t have the VISION you have for much greater things!

It’s a razor’s edge between settling and contentment.

A razor’s edge between happiness and joy.

An edge between excuses and purpose.

I look back over my life and wonder, “How’d I get this old this quickly?”

“How much longer do I have, and what am I going to do with that time?”

“Have I chosen MY path…or am I just raging against the machine?”

Yes sir, I’ve had my fair share of “bad days.”

Sometimes, it’s felt like MORE THAN my fair share…

And that’s when the PERSPECTIVE SHIFT happens.

Maybe it’s all the books I read…

Maybe it’s the willingness to get back up, just one more time…

Maybe it’s the PURPOSE I’ve found that’s bigger than me…

All I know is, when that little violin starts playing in my head, I shift from 

WHY me?

to

Why NOT me?

Apparently, I AM strong enough to find grace in this hellish situation.

I AM capable.

I AM worthy.

I AM enough.

This is just the testing ground to see if I can…

So I can, I will, I must.

Until I let go of the victimhood…

Let go of the temptation to blame…

Let go and let God.

Trusting fully that I will see how life is happening FOR me, not TO me…

And you know what, she never disappoints.
